    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing Sept<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 29<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1773.</placeName>
                </dateline>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>your kind favors of aug 23 sep<hi rend="superscript">tr.</hi> 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> &amp; 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> met me
                    yesterday at this: which with their agreable &amp; instructive contents demand
                    my best thanks. The use they are to me is very important: I have near fifty
                    Letters before me so dare say you will excuse me for not enlarging more. I can
                    only say that I feel very sensibly my inability to make an adequate return. I am
                    unwilling to force the willing horse: <sic>all I can say that if</sic> you can
                    soon pick up anything more respecting <placeName ref="pl0636">Giga</placeName>.
                    &amp;c or any of <placeName ref="pl0708">the western isles</placeName>
                    <sic>(</sic> you know those I saw it will be most acceptable. Be so good as to
                    forward the inclosed &amp; think me</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Dear Sir <lb/>with the sincerest regard <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant.</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>My compliments attend <persName ref="pe0020">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            Oliphant</persName>. also to <persName ref="pe0157">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Macgovan</persName>: the box with his kind
                        present has never been heard of: I wrote to <persName ref="pe0018">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Secretary Jackson</persName> about it;
                        begging him to write to the person who had care of it, as the loss will be
                        heavy to the poor young man. </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>Downing</p>
                <p>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            <sic>Edenburgh</sic>
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                <p>Free <lb/>
                    <persName ref="pe0113">JGlynn</persName>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <stamp type="handstamp">
                        <placeName ref="pl0002">CHESTER</placeName>
                    </stamp>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <stamp type="handstamp">
                        <placeName ref="pl0002">CHESTER</placeName>
                    </stamp>
                </p>
            </div>
